name: Northwestern University - African American Student Affairs
directions: The bathroom is located on the first floor of AASA

name: Northwestern University - Multicultural Student Affairs
directions: Located on the first floor of the MCC house

name: Joann Fabrics
directions: back left corner of the store
comment: There are two restrooms, the first restroom is considered "women" but the second is  "family" and open to all genders. Just act like you're browsing and you'll be fine.

name: University of New Haven Henry Lee Building
directions:
The building is big and grey and has huge glass doors. On the entrance level there is a forensic science display.
Through the doors, to the right and up the stairs, past room 301 and 302. There are three one room, unisex bathrooms.
comment: Technically only for students and university faculty, but the building is right near the public parking lot and most people can't tell the difference between a student and anyone else.

name: Totem Park Commons Block
directions: north end of the totem park commons block, by the gym.

name: Cedar Hall - Union Street Residence Center
directions: Ground floor, across from side entrance to the Union St Market
comment: Open to all during daytime. Also a shower!

name: Flagg Hall, SUNY Potsdam
directions: From Pierrepont Ave. entrance: Enter Saterlee Hall (the large hall in the front of the campus), turn left once you are inside, keep going that way--you will go through an exhibit on the history of the school, then there will be a staircase that leads up the stairs to the inside of Flagg. Continue down the hallway, it will be on your left.
comment: Knock to make sure nobody is in there--it's hard to tell a lot of times.

name: ASU Reich College of Education
directions: First floor and fourth floor near the elevators

name: Banana Republic
comment: pretend to know what you’re doing/shopping

name: Schlotzsky’s Deli
directions: Toilets marked Men and Women, but are one person bathrooms with good locks.
comment: you should probably/must buy something

name: Tinsel Town USA
comment: One unisex/handicapped single person bathroom with a lock in the south wing of the theater.

name: South Plains College Reese Campus
comment: Other notes If you are transgender and speak to Valerie Cox, a counselor on the Reese campus, she will talk to the dean for you to make arrangements for you to be able to use the bathroom that you identify as. I have been told that if I have any problems using the men’s bathroom I can contact Reese’s dean and he will take care of it. As long as they are aware of the issue, I haven’t had any problems using the bathroom that I wish. There are also a few gender neutral bathrooms on campus.

name: Covenant Lakeside Hospital
comment:
Signage: ‘toilet’ with both man & woman sign plus cheelchair
Notes: Single Unit, Locked Door, Totally safe for any gender

name: Firestone
comment: Signage:  ‘toilet’ with both man & woman sign

name: Grace Clinic
directions: There are many gendered bathrooms, but at least 1 neutral.  The one I’m reporting here is next to room #111 across from imaging.
comment: Signage: man & woman sign

name: SPCAA/Project CHAMPS
comment: This toilet is reserved for the clients, their friends & family of Project CHAMPS. Project CHAMPS is proud to be one of the few agencies in Lubbock with “gender identity” and “gender expression” included in our non-discrimination clause.

name: Mary Ward Hall
directions: In lobby
comment: This is an on-campus residence hall. Ask the person at the front desk if you could just use the restroom and they will point it out. You do not need to be a resident to use the lobby restroom.

name: Mary Park Hall
directions: In lobby
comment: This is an on-campus residence hall. Ask the person at the front desk if you could just use the restroom and they will point it out. You do no need to be a resident to use the lobby restroom.

name: Swarthmore Co-op
directions: In the back corner
comment: Two gendered bathrooms, both single room

name: Hip City Veg
directions: In the back, left of registers
comment: Two single-room unisex bathrooms

name: The Beanery (Circle St.)
directions: back of the cafe between the register counter and seating area.
comment: wheelchair accessible but may need to go through register line area depending on table arrangement.

name: University of Illinois at Chicago
directions: Fourth floor
comment: Designated as a nonbinary safe space by the Gender and Sexuality Center

name: What? Cafe
directions: The cafe is located on the corner of MLK and Tharpe in the Northwood Plaza, not on Monroe itself. It is behind the ProBank and across the street from the post office. When you come in, the restrooms are on the left, behind the half wall.
comment: This is a small, locally owned business. If you cannot afford to buy something, please at least let people know about the cafe.

name: Roberts Dormitory
directions: Use main entrance to Roberts dorm (northeast side of building) during normal business hours to go into a small lobby. Bathroom is through a small anteroom to the left after entering.
comment: Main entrance of building should be open to public during normal business hours (M-F 8-5); at any other time must have access through a resident

name: University of Texas Student Union
directions: Third level inside the Sinclair Suite (3.128), toward the back of the room
comment: there may be student groups meeting in the Sinclair Suite. Most probably wouldn't mind if you go through quickly and quietly, though.

name: Juliens Bakery
directions: To the Righthand side and down some stairs. Ask for key.
comment: Ask or be discreet if not paying.

name: Starbucks
directions: To the back. Two bathrooms and I believe they are unmarked.
comment: Be discreet or ask if you are not paying

name: Trident Cafe
directions: To the Left and Back
comment: Books and coffee together! And Buddhists! They'll understand.

name: Paperchase cafe
directions: Through the magazine store, up the stairs, keep turning Right
comment: Not the cleanest but interesting graffitti

name: Steve O Reno's Cappucchinos
directions: Head to the lefthand side of the cafe, go to the back.
comment: Be discreet if you are not paying.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: There are 2 unisex bathrooms on the right side at the back of the store.

name: Local Jos
directions: Two bathrooms, one upstairs, one downstairs. It's a pretty small cafe.
comment: Just ask nicely. Warning that this is a family friendly cafe = babies

name: Creative Commons studio/business centre
directions: From Agricola street, remain on the first floor. Head back, it will be on your right past the stairs. Or ask at EnVie vegan resto
comment: A closet of a bathroom, shared by studios and businesses. Pretty much public.

name: Organic Earth natural foods
directions: All the way to the Righthand side, all the way to the back.
comment: Nobody ever checks if you're a customer or not.

name: Alteregos cafe
directions: Between the cafe and the hostel
comment: Should be fine

name: Java Blend
directions: In the roasting room, follow the silver tape arrows on the floor.
comment: Easygoing

name: Plan B
directions: On the left (south) side of the building, toward the back.
comment: Gendered, but noone gives a fuck. Noone.

name: The Wallflower
directions: At the back of the dining area.
comment: For paying customers. While the bathroom itself is accessible, getting through the dining space to it is a bit hard.

name: Just Us Cafe
directions: Three restrooms, two on first floor one on top floor (not accessible except by stair)
comment: Pretty flexible

name: Bossy Grrl's PinUp Joint
directions: Past the bar/cooler, through the doorway and on the right.

name: Rickert & Beagle Books
directions: In the front door and straight back, it's a tiny space so the bathroom is easy to find.
comment: I am posting this as the owner of the store. If you need access to my bathroom come in and use my bathroom!

name: Cinemark Egyptian 24
directions: down the main hallway of theaters on either side there's a 'family' bathroom with a locking door and a stall divider.
comment: Most ticket tearers will let you in, some will let you in if you leave something like your keys with them, some won't without a ticket. (With the first forty minutes of any movie you can get a refund for a ticket so if you really have to, you can buy a ticket and then go to Guest Services and get a refund.

name: Good Shepherd Center
directions: Three Options, One in the basement/first floor (accessible) by the South Stairwell, One on the second floor (accessible) by the South Stairwell, and one on the third floor which is stalled, gender-neutral, but there is a step to enter that bathroom, On the North end by all the therapists offices.
comment: Building is generally open from 8am to 8pm except on most holidays.

name: Civic Theatre of Allentown
directions: There are 2 movie theatres across the street from each other, the theatre has 2 lockable unisex bathrooms
comment: Not all attendants will allow non-patrons to use the bathrooms during show time, but most will.

name: Northampton Community College
directions: Second floor between the cafeteria and disability resources office, near the stairs going to the 'Spartan Center'.
comment: Just act like a student.

name: Chromatic
directions: Straight to the back

name: Copeley Lounge
comment: Must be a resident of Copeley III & IV undergraduate dorms at the University of Virginia

name: San Francisco Airport
directions: inside terminals on both sides of security there are "companion care" bathrooms that are private and GN

name: San Leandro BART Station
directions: inside to the right by the stairs
comment: inside BART turnstile

name: Fine Arts Performance Facilities York University
directions: walk in through the South East entrance its about ten paces from the door on your right.

name: CCA
directions: Ground floor, to the left of the bar.

name: Berkeley High School Health Center
directions: You have to ask the secretary at the front desk before you can go through to the bathroom.
comment: Only available to Berkeley High School students.

name: 924 Gilman
directions: On the right side of the room when facing the stage. Two gender neutral multiple-stall bathrooms, one with urinals, one without.
comment: Gilman is supposed to be a trans-friendly venue, but occasionally assholes show up. Be wary, depending on the show you're at.

name: Berkeley Community Media
directions: Just to the left when coming in through the front door.
comment: It's a public access TV station, very LGBTQ-friendly. They let folks come in just to use the bathroom (no need to pretend that you're interested).

name: Philz Coffee
directions: To the right of the counter/register. You have to get the key at the register.
comment: You should probably get some coffee. The people here are super nice though and I have used it in the past without paying. Just come in, hang out for a bit and then go up and ask for the key. This is a really awesome location to get coffee too.

name: Southpark Mall
directions: Bathrooms next to Food Court and near Sur La Table have unisex 'Family' Restrooms

name: Plato's Closet
directions: Past the dressing rooms. ask an employee to unlock it

name: Regal Cinemas 14
directions: When you walk into the building, it is at the end of the hallway to your left.
comment: Must have a ticket for a movie in order to gain access to restrooms.

name: LSUS science building
directions: Each of the three floors in the science building have one unisex/accessable restroom
comment: On the bottom floor, you can find it in the center of the building. On the 2nd and 3rd floors, they are near the staircase towards the back of campus.

name: Save-A-Lot
directions: Walk in the door and go directly back, next to the meat coolers

name: Sam's Club
directions: Near the food court, front of the store, may be difficult to locate if you don’t see the sign right away
comment: You may be asked for your membership card at the door, but you may also be able to tell them you're going to apply for one and they'll let you in

name: Colony Square Mall
directions: Near Hat World in the food court

name: Big Lots
directions: Back corner of the store near the furniture section

name: Walmart
directions: Through the electronics section and near/inside the photo lab
comment: MAKE SURE the door is locked; the lock does not work very well

name: Walmart
directions: Very back of the store, through the photo section

name: The Outlets at Louisiana Boardwalk
directions: ground floor of parking garage

name: Indiana University South Bend - Arts and Education Building
directions: From the front of the building, go past the Starbucks and student seating to the first hallway. Single-stall "family" bathroom will be on the right.

name: Bellefield Hall
directions:
Second floor has two unisex restrooms on the north side, near the weight room. 

One is a former men's room, and is still frequently used by male students to change for the gym. The other is the accessible locker room next door; go through the locker room into the bathroom, which is a single-toilet + shower.  Both are lockable.
comment: Bellefield Hall requires Pitt ID for 'recreational use', but classes, purchasing software from the Student Software Sales office, and visiting offices are exempt.  Offices in the building include  University Times, CSSD administration, campus YMCA, and Army ROTC.

name: Rosslyn Starbucks
directions: Across from counter

name: Art Kitchen
directions: Back right side wall.
comment: The cookies are delicious! Give them some love with a small purchase if ya can^^

name: Butter Bakery/Cafe
comment: At least one staff member (afternoon/evening cook, as of winter '14) has a trans* family member.

name: Outpost Natural Foods
directions: Go in the door and turn left, it is in the corner past the indoor seating area.
comment: Just go on in! I work here, we don't mind.

name: Center for Intercultural Organizinf
directions: As you enter the front door, there's a hallway on the right side. Go down that hall and make a right before the kitchen.
comment: We're a social justice nonprofit, and anyone's welcome to come in. We might hand you a pamphlet about our work, but that's about it.

name: Joyce Layland lgbt centre
directions: Second door on the right towards the back.
comment: Open Wednesday Thursday Friday. Its a cafe staffed by lovely people.

name: UBC Student Union Building
directions: Rooms 111E,  127d and 253c

name: UBC ICICS Comp Science
directions: Third floor in the back

name: Target
directions: North side by the cold food cases/milk/booze/etc
comment: Always clean, security camera watching corridor, you don't have to buy anything, and most customers use the icky WCs at the front of the store and don't know it's there.

name: Java Roaster
directions: Ground floor, in the back on the left
comment: You should probably buy a coffee...  The mochas are good.

name: Terra Patio
directions: Back hallway, second door on the left.
comment: Pretend to browse on weekends. Just ask for a restroom on weekdays.

name: Coffee Bar
directions: to the right of the counter as you face it
comment: it can get a little crowded here so waiting for the bathroom may be a bit awkward if you don't buy anything

name: Arbor Cafe
directions: In the back

name: The Daily Grind
directions: Walk in and head to the right, the bathroom is in the small room right off the main area.
comment: You don't have to buy anything to use it! (at least they've never seemed to make a big deal out of it)

name: Tucker Hall
directions: Third floor, you have to take the elevator all the way up but there are unisex bathrooms on both ends of the 3rd floor hall.

name: Rick's Cantina
directions: Second floor, in the back to the left

name: Moscow Pullman Regional Airport
directions: Between two gender segregated bathrooms is a gender neutral family restroom.

name: Fox Valley Unitarian Universalist Fellowship
directions: Ring for entrance and we'll buzz you in!
comment: We tend to be open between 8-3 M-F, on Saturday afternoon/evening and Sunday morning/early afternoon. We're a genderqueer and trans* positive space and invite you to join us if you need a restroom! We have private stall bathrooms as well as multi-user ones with trans* inclusive signage.

name: the old crow cafe
directions: at the back; the owner is usually working and is super cool. the food is yummy and cheap, too.

name: Shell / Smart mart
directions: Inside right rear
comment: Men and woman restrooms very clean Marble Floors and Walls open 24 hrs!!!!!

name: Hanabi
directions: Straight in past the host area to the left.
comment: Mon-Thur 11am-10pmFri-Sat 11am-11pmSun 12pm-Close (not sure when close is but that's what it said on the website‰Û_)Cool, Welcoming Place

name: Arlington Velo Sport Bicycle Shop
directions: It's a little complicated to get there, but you can just ask.  They only have gender-neutral bathrooms, so you don't really have to specify that if you don't want to.  There's a door behind the employee's work area, and then there's a bit of a maze to go through, but there are two genderfree bathrooms back there!

name: Casa Brandon
comment: Open at night. Trans safe space.

name: Portland Loo (#2)
street: SW Naito Parkway at SW Ash Street
comment: PORTLAND LOOs are simple, sturdy,flush toilet kiosks located on sidewalksin public areas. The loos are free to the public and accessible every day of the year. Portland Loos give thecommunity environmentally-friendly,clean, and safe restroom facilities.PORTLAND LOOs are open 24 hours a day,365 days a yearPORTLAND LOOs have handwashing stations mounted on the exterior to serve the pedestrian population PORTLAND LOOs are cleaned twice a dayPORTLAND LOOs are ADA-accessible and can fit a bicycle or stroller comfortably inside.

name: Tramps
directions: Back on main floor.
comment: Open 7 days a week. It's prefered if you buy something or attend weekly gaming sessions to create a report with the community.
